ZH: 夏天来临时，树叶褪去了翠绿的颜色，变成了黄色。
EN: When summer comes, the leaves fade from green to yellow.

ZH: 大雪将山顶上的白花花的雪峰褪去了它们的光辉。
EN: The heavy snow stripped the dazzling snow-capped peaks of their glory.

ZH: 玫瑰花在凋谢时花瓣会褪去颜色，最后只剩下花蕊。
EN: The petals of rose flowers fade in color when they wither, revealing only the pistil.

ZH: 时间会慢慢褪去我们的记忆，渐渐成为过去。
EN: Time will gradually fade away our memories and become the past.

ZH: 随着岁月的流逝，他的热情渐渐褪去。
EN: With the passage of time, his passion gradually faded away.

ZH: 长时间处于阳光下会导致颜色褪去。
EN: Prolonged exposure to sunlight can cause colors to fade.

ZH: 这部电影的场景褪去了色彩，显得格外沉闷。
EN: The scenes in this movie have faded in color, making it particularly dull.

ZH: 慢慢适应了新环境后，她停止了思乡的念头，褪去了对家的思念。
EN: After gradually adjusting to the new environment, she stopped missing home and the longing faded away.

ZH: 这幅画已经褪去了原先的光彩，需要进行修复。
EN: This painting has faded from its original brilliance and needs restoration.

ZH: 这件衣服已经被太阳晒得褪去了颜色。
EN: The sun has bleached the color out of this piece of clothing.

ZH: 预测仪器的准确度随着时间的推移而褪去了光芒。
EN: The accuracy of the forecasting instrument has faded over time.

ZH: 这首歌曲在很长时间后依然能让人回想起美好的回忆，没有褪去魅力。
EN: Even after a long time, this song can still evoke beautiful memories without fading in charm.

ZH: 年老时，人们的视力和听力往往会褪去。
EN: As people age, their vision and hearing often fade.

ZH: 责任感也会随着时间的流逝而褪去，遗留下安逸与放松。
EN: Sense of responsibility can also fade away with the passage of time, leaving behind comfort and relaxation.

ZH: 病痛的折磨逐渐褪去，她恢复了活力。
EN: The torment of illness gradually faded, and she regained her vitality.

ZH: 雨水冲刷的力量将污渍褪去，留下一片清新。
EN: The force of rainwater washes away the stains, leaving behind a fresh look.

ZH: 公园里的绿树随着季节的变化，叶子颜色会褪去再重新变回绿色。
EN: The green trees in the park change color with the seasons, fading and then turning green again.

ZH: 长时间使用的红色汽车会逐渐褪去色彩，显得不如新车鲜艳。
EN: A red car that has been used for a long time will gradually fade in color, appearing less vibrant than a new car.

ZH: 历史的洪流无法褪去英雄人物的光辉。
EN: The course of history cannot strip away the glory of heroic figures.

ZH: 我们要拥抱未来，但不应该忘记过去，不可褪去历史的痕迹。
EN: We should embrace the future but not forget the past. We mustn't erase the traces of history.
